00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:42,160
Because they left him to die.

265
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:47,159
A member of the excavation team of the hidden treasures of Tokugawa,

266
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:50,359
as well as my husband,

267
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:52,360
Charles Abel.

268
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:57,759
Then, don't tell me that...

269
00:14:57,760 --> 00:15:00,359
those two were also members of the excavation team?

270
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:03,159
Yes. At the time of the cave-in accident,

271
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:06,059
the ones that left my husband to die were those two.

272
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:08,859
My husband was still alive then, and yet...

273
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:09,959
But...

274
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,159
It couldn't be helped, could it?

275
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:18,959
Because he wrote the word Nue on the paper.

276
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,559
That wasn't Nue.

277
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:23,660
He wrote iron, right?

278
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:32,459
Charles actually wanted to write that he found a iron hairpin.

279
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:35,659
But being a foreigner he never saw one.

280
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:37,459
So, after writing "iron",

281
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:40,959
I think he wanted to show the word written on the paper

282
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:44,259
and ask the excavators what it was.

283
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:47,359
He wrote very slowly using a permanent marker,

284
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,959
so the ink smudged and bled through the back side.

285
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,759
Therefore, the other members mistakenly thought

286
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,759
that he wrote the word Nue.

287
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:56,159
I see.

288
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,659
You took advantage of the fact that they mistook him

289
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:01,959
and lured the two over here, right?

290
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,759
By writing them a letter

291
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:06,759
saying that Charles may have found an iron jar.

292
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,359
An iron jar?

293
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,259
Did you forget?

294
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:11,459
The light of dawn seeps through.

295
00:16:11,460 --> 00:16:14,359
The light of the sunset shines on 2,000 such jars

296
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:18,159
filled with 1,000 gold coins.

297
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:20,359
This nursery rhyme. If there are 1000 coins in the jar,

298
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,959
that's some treasure.

299
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:25,960
So, lured by that the two came along.

300
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:28,759
Not even aware that they were going to be killed.

301
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:33,459
Yes. I was planning to let them go if they didn't show up but,

302
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:36,659
they had the nerve to come over.

303
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:40,159
By the way, you called the detective to make him testify

304
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,659
that the monster really existed.

305
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:44,459
And you also told him to bring his young girlfriend along

306
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:49,659
so that she would see the creepy hiragana practice book and panic.

307
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:52,359
After she panicked and asked to have the room changed you figured that...

308
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,959
Mr. Tanzawa would want to move to the room

309
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,059
with Charles's belongings inside,

310
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:58,159
so he might find more clues on the iron jar.

311
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:00,559
Therefore, you assumed that he would move over

312
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,059
to the room exactly above yours,

313
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:04,559
making it easier to poison him to death.

314
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,559
Then, why did you invite me,

315
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,859
a reportage writer that has nothing to do with this?

316
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:11,359
That's probably because...

317
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:14,459
Ms. Masuko is...

318
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:16,160
your mother.

319
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,459
I think she wanted to show you

320
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:22,760
that she was avenging your father's death.

321
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:27,259
That dog liked you a lot probably

322
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:31,360
because you looked a lot like its owner who died.

323
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,659
No joke? Are you serious?

324
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:40,159
Ridiculous. No way.

325
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:43,159
I read your poor reportage

326
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:45,960
and called you over just in fun.

327
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:55,760
So, go on and write a good reportage this time...

328
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:59,859
about a stupid lady who tried to take advantage

329
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:01,959
of the legend of a monster,

330
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,860
and got a taste of her own medicine.

331
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:14,060
It's just like in the legend.

332
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:17,259
According to an account,

333
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:22,159
Nue is the transformed figure of Yorimasa Minamoto's mother

334
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:27,160
who wanted to give him credit for an achievement.

335
00:19:56,460 --> 00:20:01,359
Aren't you Ran and Conan?

336
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:03,059
Yes.

337
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:08,259
This is a grave case, and yet, where is Mr. Mouri?

338
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:10,559
He's not here.

339
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,059
I mean did you just realize now?

340
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:15,259
Hey, Conan.

341
00:20:15,260 --> 00:20:17,059
Have you seen Kazuha?

342
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:22,059
Yeah, she went along with Heiji towards Kurogane Ooike.

343
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:26,759
But, I think you should leave them alone for now.

344
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,159
Watch how I do things carefully, okay!

345
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,860
He was saying...

346
00:20:40,060 --> 00:20:44,359
What is it, Heiji, calling me out to a place like this?

347
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:46,659
If you're planning to show me another strange monster,

348
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:48,459
I've already had enough of it!

349
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:50,559
No, stupid.

350
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:54,160
I'm only going to say this once, so listen well, okay!

351
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,660
Well, Kazuha...

352
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:23,660
The surface of the water of the lake

353
00:21:23,661 --> 00:21:25,659
